collectRentAllTokens().details: basically functions that have checkState(States.OPEN) modifiermakes it easy for me to call whenever I want to keep people paying their rent, thus cannot be internalcannot be external because it is called within the step1 functions, therefore public

complete().details: users pull dai into their ac   count.

depositDai(uint256,uint256).details: it is possible a user's deposit could be reduced to zero following _collectRentthey would then increase their deposit despite no longer owning itthis is ok, they can still withdraw via withdrawDeposit. can be called by anyone- you can top up someone else's deposit if you wish!

exit(uint256).details: do not need to be the current ownerno modifiers because they are on withdrawDeposit

returns._0: how much the current owner has deposited

rentOwed(uint256).details: called in collectRent function, and various other view functions

returns._0: how much the current user has deposited (note: user not owner)

withdrawDeposit(uint256,uint256).details: do not need to be the current ownerpublic because called by exit

withdrawDepositAfterMarketEnded().details: the other withdraw deposit functions are locked when markets have closed so must use this onecan be called in either locked or withdraw statethis function is also different in that it does ... not attempt to collect rent or transfer ownership to a previous owner

changePrice(uint256,uint256).notice: increase the price of an existing rental

complete().notice: the final function of the competition resolution process. Pays out winnings, or returns funds, as necessary

depositDai(uint256,uint256).notice: add new dai deposit to an existing rental

mintNfts(string).notice: ///////////////////////////////// ///// INITIAL SETUP ///////////// /////////////////////////////////mint the NFTs. Must setTokenOwner first or will revert

step1checkMarketEnded().notice: ///////////////////////////////// / MARKET RESOLUTION FUNCTIONS /// /////////////////////////////////the first of two functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionwinnings can be paid out (or funds returned) only when these two steps are completedthis function checks whether the competition has ended (1 hour grace), if so closes down all 'ordinary course of business' functions

step2BemergencyExit().notice: emergency function in case the Realitio question never resolves for whatever reason, can be called by anyonereturns all funds to all userscan only be called 1 month after Realitio question should have ended

step2CcircuitBreaker().notice: Same as above, except that only owner can call it, and can be called at any timeto be clear, this only allows owner to return all funds, not to set a winner

step2getWinner().notice: the second of two functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionthis function checks whether the Realitio question has resolved, and if yes, gets the winner

withdrawDepositAfterMarketEnded().notice: withdraw full deposit after markets have resolved
